name: Midwinter Coffee Set
description:
Midwinter 'Roselle' design from 1968. Coffee pot with three cups and saucers. The coffee pot has a light blue lid and all have a matching floral design The saucers are a shiny dark blue.

One cup has a small chip to the lip, some signs of wear commensurate with age. It's still a lovely set which would look lovely in any setting.

Measurements - Coffee Pot: 10cm wide x 18cm high. Cup: 7cm wide x 7cm high. Saucer: 15cm radius.

name: Green Triangle
description:
A lovingly hand embroidered piece of artwork, with dashes of bright colour for a modern twist.

Created by Ruth Baxter. Exclusive colourway to Studio Hunting Bears.

Each individual piece is hand embroidered onto premium heavy white card, signed and hand numbered by the artist. 

There are only fifteen available.

Please note that this print is hand made, therefore will take time to produce.

The print will fit a standard Ikea Ribba frame for ease, which are available in different finishes - the frame in the photograph is white. Frame size is 30 x 40cm and aperture size is 20 x 29cm. Please note, frames are not included with the print.

Posted direct from the artist.

Due to the delicate nature of the artwork keep out of direct sunlight and frame behind glass.

Hand numbered and initialled by the artist.

name: Girl with a Feather Earring
